      <hedline>
        <hl1>Pausing to Remember a Cardinal</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Cardinal O'Connor, 80, Dies; Forceful Voice for Vatican'' (front page, May 4):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Cardinal O'Connor, 80, Dies; Forceful Voice for Vatican'' (front page, May 4):</p>
        <p>I am a Jew, and I feel as if I have lost a friend. Cardinal John O'Connor, more than almost any other prelate, made it clear that anti-Semitism is a sin and that all prejudice is an attack on the human person he loved so much.</p>
        <p>He was instrumental in establishing relations between Israel and the Vatican, a movement long overdue. He championed the dignity of work, which was so in keeping with Roman Catholic moral theology.</p>
        <p>While I disagreed with his stance on many issues, his overall ministry to all of us, Christian and Jew alike, will stand as a shining moment in this city's history.</p>
        <p>KAREN SILVER  Bronx, May 4, 2000</p>
      </block>
